76561197971341065,Recommended,569610,28498044,"Posted: 20 December, 2016",all,sfnhltb,"Space Distant is a fairly basic Space Invaders update, although not all that much of an update, and it is inferior to the original in a few ways, although it has a few good points as well. You aren't likely to get a huge amount of play time out of it, but it is okay for what it is.You get three repetitions of five levels of growing difficulty (mostly more shots raining down from more alien types) then a boss fight - the normal waves are fairly easy although you have to take care as you have three lives to clear all 18 levels - as unlike the original the aliens don't advance down the screen you can play it safe in the middle of the screen and take your time picking them off - each alien type fires in a different way, and the more powerful ones take a few hits to go down as well, which tends to make the sides of the screen dangerous particularly when certain alien types are present. You do also (randomly?) get a triple shot attack for a short while when you kill an alien (or a missile), which can help clear the screen fast.The boss fights are a bit more interesting (and difficult) as you have the combination of a constant rain of shots you have to stay ahead of and dodge between to keep attacking the boss, but also after a short while the boss will also launch missiles (which you can shoot or feint and dodge), and then start doing both at once, which is where it gets difficult not to get hit. The bosses look different but seem to behave the same - well, the first two did as far as I noticed, haven't got to the third yet - and that may take a while as the green wave aliens make things tough in level 14.The controls are fairly responsive, and the graphics are basic but clear, apart from the one exception of the cyan enemies shot coming down being fairly hard to notice if you are shooting in place, but overall this is fine for what it is, but don't expect to play it for long (or more than once), and there is little innovation or interesting in this example of a very well trodden genre."
