,Recommended,569610,28497609,"Posted: 20 December, 2016",all,Redbeard,"Space Distant is a retro-styled version of Space Invaders.There's not a lot to it - just the usual case of shoot down the aliens before they get you.Some of the bigger aliens take more than one shot to kill.Several aliens shoot diagonally.The first boss is massive and has heat-seeking missiles(Apparently there is a second boss - at level 15? - but I haven't got that far yet.)Although Space Distant doesn't specify what controls the game uses, after having spent thousands of dollars on exhaustive research and private investigators, I can now reveal that they are:Spacebar = shootArrow keys = move left and rightThis game is not one you would want to play over and over again.But, then again, it has achievements, so you might want to play it a few times to get those.It's a cheap game, just under a dollar, so you can't go too wrong with it - however, considering how basic it is, I would have thought that 50 cents would be more reasonable.For a cheap game it's ok, but nothing more than that."
